window.VERDICTS = {"icon-of-the-seas|titanic":"Icon of the Seas is about five times the Titanic's tonnage and 96 m longer — the century of shipbuilding between them in one picture. Titanic keeps one number: at ≈23 knots flat out she was the faster ship.","icon-of-the-seas|legend-of-the-seas":"A foot of length is the entire difference — Legend measured out fractionally longer at delivery in 2026 and took the world's-largest title from inside her own class. Tonnage, capacity and crew are identical.","icon-of-the-seas|wonder-of-the-seas":"Icon out-measures Wonder by ≈12,000 GT and three metres of length, but Wonder carries more people at double occupancy — 5,734 to 5,610. Volume and capacity are different records, and they split here.","queen-mary-2|titanic":"QM2 is the ship Titanic's designers would recognise instantly — a true North Atlantic liner — at three times the tonnage and seven knots faster in service. Ninety-two years separate the only two liners on this site.","icon-of-the-seas|seawise-giant":"The tanker is nearly 94 m longer — the length gap is almost exactly one football pitch — but Icon is the larger ship by internal volume. Longest ever versus biggest cruise ship: both records, one picture.","ever-alot|ever-given":"Sisters in brand, a generation apart in packing: same 400 m envelope, but Alot is rated for 3,880 more TEU. Ever Given's fame is the only category she wins.","emma-maersk|msc-irina":"Seventeen years between them, two metres of length — and roughly 9,000 more TEU on Irina. The container revolution's second act happened almost entirely inside the same hull dimensions.","ever-alot|msc-irina":"342 TEU is the whole gap — a couple of deck rows. The record at the top of container shipping now moves in rounding errors, and these two are the proof.","icon-of-the-seas|queen-mary-2":"Icon has 100,000 more gross tons and twice the passengers; QM2 has ten knots of speed and a hull built for a North Atlantic January. A resort and a vehicle, drawn to the same scale.","prelude-flng|seawise-giant":"Prelude is ≈30 m longer and will never sail a metre — she was towed to Australia and moored for life. Longest floating structure versus longest ship: this site scores them as different records, drawn here at true scale.","batillus|pierre-guillaumat":"Twins to the centimetre — Guillaumat carries the deadweight record by 1,389 t on measurement, and both were scrapped before their tenth birthdays. The whole tragedy of maximum scale in one comparison.","seawise-giant|ti-europe":"The last ULCC afloat against the ghost she replaced: Seawise Giant was 78 m longer and lifted 120,000 t more, but TI Europe is double-hulled, still trading, and still the largest working ship on Earth.","berge-stahl|vale-brasil":"The 2011 Valemax out-lifts the 1986 champion by ≈37,000 t on a hull 20 m longer — a quarter-century of ore-carrier evolution, and the moment the two-port shuttle era ended.","cma-cgm-jacques-saade|mozah":"Both carry LNG — Mozah as 266,000 m³ of cargo, Jacques Saadé as 18,600 m³ of fuel under 23,112 boxes. The gas trade and the gas-powered future, side by side.","icon-of-the-seas|pioneering-spirit":"The widest ship ever built against the biggest cruise ship: Pioneering Spirit is 2.5× the beam and 155,000 GT larger — the largest ship in history carries no cargo and no passengers.","icon-of-the-seas|oasis-of-the-seas":"Fifteen years between the ship that invented the mega-resort and the class that perfected it: ≈22,000 more GT on Icon, LNG power, and the same split-superstructure DNA visible in both profiles.","ever-ace|hmm-algeciras":"Twenty-eight TEU decided this record in 2021. Algeciras held the crown for fifteen months; Ace took it by less than one bay of boxes.","exxon-valdez|ti-europe":"The single-hulled ship whose grounding wrote the rules, against the largest double-hull ever built under them. Every tanker since 1990 is shaped by what happened to the smaller of these two."};
window.COMPARE_PAGES = ["icon-of-the-seas|titanic","icon-of-the-seas|legend-of-the-seas","queen-mary-2|titanic","icon-of-the-seas|seawise-giant","ever-alot|ever-given","emma-maersk|msc-irina"];
